### Mechanics

At [Valve](/Valve_Corporation), a rather striking visual and practical representation of their open allocation philosophy is the presence of wheels beneath employees' desks. This design choice facilitates the effortless relocation of their workstations to join different teams as project needs dictate, serving as both a symbolic and tangible manifestation of their fluid organizational structure.

A significant portion of [GitHub](/GitHub) employees operate as [remote workers](/Remote_work), meaning team affiliation is, to a degree, determined by participation in specific [chat rooms](/Chat_room).

[Treehouse](/Treehouse_(company)) permits any team member to switch teams at their discretion. However, they strongly discourage, deeming it "not cool," abandoning a team during a critical juncture or when one's colleagues are in need. Such an action, it's noted, would inevitably be reflected in subpar performance reviews.

